I'm an administrator on [[w:User:OhanaUnited|English Wikipedia]] and bureaucrat on [[:species:User:OhanaUnited|WikiSpecies]]. If you need help on these 2 projects, just drop me a message in my talk page (preferably in the corresponding project's talk page which you require help on).

import_script('User:Whiteknight/gadgetscore.js');
import_script('User:Whiteknight/categorize.js');
import_script('User:Whiteknight/designer3.js');

/* Random Book Finder, version [0.0.4a-r3]
Originally from: http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/User:Splarka/randbook.js
Based roughly on http://en.wikibooks.org/w/index.php?title=MediaWiki:RandomBook.js&oldid=1209572 by Darklama.

Notes:
* Grab only 10 random pages in one go because that is the limit.
* 2 iterations may be needed because 10.5% of pages are books.
* Refer to books by their ID to find them even when moved.
* Append links instead with: mw.config.set( 'random_book_list', true ); (add this in your [[Special:MyPage/common.js]]);
*/

$(document).ready( function($) {
	var	reqid = 0, random_list = mw.config.get( 'random_book_list', false ),
		randbookLink = mw.util.addPortletLink( 'p-Navigation', '#', 'Random book', 'n-randbook', 'Show me a random book', 'x' ),
		bookLink = mw.config.get( 'wgServer' ) + mw.config.get( 'wgScript' ) + '?curid=';

	function fetch_categories( id, callback ) {
		$.getJSON( mw.util.wikiScript( 'api' ), {
			format:		'json',
			action:		'query',
			prop:		'categories',
			cllimit:	100,
			generator:	'random',
			grnnamespace:	'0|110',
			grnlimit:	10,
			requestid:	id
		}, callback );
	}

	function showRandBookCB(obj) {
		var pages;

		if ( !obj.query || !obj.query.pages ) {
			$(randbookLink).append('<span class="error">error</span>');
			if ( random_list ) {
				removeSpinner( 'randbook' );
			}
			return;
		}

		pages = $.map( obj.query.pages, function(page, id) {
			return $.map( page.categories || [], function( cat ) {
				if ( cat.title.indexOf( 'Category:Alphabetical/' ) === 0 ) {
					return { id: id, title: page.title };
				}
			});
		});

		if ( !pages.length ) {
			// didn't find any, try again
			++reqid;
			fetch_categories( reqid, showRandBookCB );
			return;
		}

		if ( !random_list ) {
			window.location.assign( bookLink + pages[ Math.floor( Math.random()*pages.length ) ].id );
			return;
		}

		removeSpinner( 'randbook' );
		$.each( pages, function() {
			$(randbookLink).append('<div><a href="' + bookLink + this.id + '"> \u2022\u00A0' + this.title + '</a></div>');
		});
	}

	$(randbookLink).click( function(e) {
		if ( random_list ) {
			injectSpinner( this, 'randbook' );
		}
		++reqid;
		fetch_categories( reqid, showRandBookCB );
		e.preventDefault();
	});
});

==== log ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double log( double num );
</source>
}}

The function log() returns the natural (base e) logarithm of ''num''. There's a domain error if ''num'' is negative, a range error if ''num'' is zero.

In order to calculate the logarithm of x to an arbitrary base b, you can use:

<source lang=cpp>
double answer = log(x) / log(b);
</source>

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/exp|exp]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/log10|log10]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/pow|pow]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sqrt|sqrt]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== log10 ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double log10( double num );
</source>
}}

The <code>log10()</code> function returns the base 10 (or common) logarithm for <code>num</code>. There will be a domain error if <code>num</code> is negative and a range error if <code>num</code> is zero.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/log|log]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== pow ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double pow( double base, double exp );
</source>
}}

The pow() function returns ''base'' raised to the ''exp''th power. There's a domain error if base is zero and ''exp'' is less than or equal to zero. There's also a domain error if base is negative and ''exp'' is not an integer. There's a range error if an overflow occurs.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/exp|exp]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/log|log]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sqrt|sqrt]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== sqrt ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double sqrt( double num );
</source>
}}

The sqrt() function returns the square root of ''num''. If ''num'' is negative, a domain error occurs.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/exp|exp]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/log|log]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/pow|pow]]

