* Python Pil library functions for reading GIMP gradient files ( in file GimpGradientFile.py) 
* [http://www.mail-archive.com/gimp-user@lists.xcf.berkeley.edu/msg03062.html perl scripts to convert gimp-1.2.x palettes and gradients into a 1.3 form  by Jeff Trefftzs]
* [http://xoomer.virgilio.it/lwcon/gimp/python/make-gradient.htm Gimp Python plugin: make-gradient.py by Giuseppe Conte]
* [http://ygingras.net/fract gimp gradient files - lisp code from Polypen by Yannick Gingras]
* [http://git.gnome.org/browse/gimp/tree/tools/pdbgen/pdb/gradient.pdb Perl functions from GIMP pdb - gradient.pdb]

===Collections of gradients ===
* [http://sourceforge.net/projects/gradcentral/ gradcentral ]
* [http://soliton.vm.bytemark.co.uk/pub/cpt-city/ Cpt-city]
* gimp gradients (ggr files) are in directory : /usr/share/gimp/2.0/gradients/

