==Plug-in Options== <!-- image -->
The plug-in tab allows you to load or unload one or more KTorrent plug-ins. As you load or unload plug-ins, configuration tabs are added or removed in the preferences dialog. If memory is an issue on your computer, disabling unused plug-ins will free memory.
{{BookCat}}

==Log viewer plug-in== <!--image--> The log viewer tab has options to adjust the level of output in the log viewer panel. To adjust the logging output, you can choose from pre-defined profiles which can be set on any of the filters in system or plug-ins.
Use Rich Text For Log is a setting to make some messages to appear in gray. It can make the information inside the log viewer easier to read.
{{BookCat}}

==Search plug-in== The search tab allows you to edit, remove, or add search engines to KTorrent. After you add your favorite torrent search engine, you can use the search panel (located to the left of the normal KTorrent interface) to search for torrents using your selected search engine.
The external browser section allows you to configure which browser should be opened by default when you do a search and Open External web browser is set. Use default browser will use your computer's default web browser.
{{BookCat}}

==Scheduler plug-in==
You can disable or enable this plug-in, and with the Edit Schedule button, you can load the current scheduling in a dialog with all the options needed to edit it properly.

{{BookCat}}

==IP blocking filter==
The IP blocking filter tab allows you to configure the IP filter by using a downloaded filter file, converting the downloaded file to a binary file for better performance, and to select the location where the filter file is located.

{{BookCat}}
